<h2>Solar Incentives in Fort Lauderdale</h2>

<p>Fort Lauderdale residents can take advantage of several solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, available through 2032. Florida offers additional benefits including no state income tax on solar installations, property tax exemption for added home value from solar systems, and sales tax exemption on solar equipment purchases. FPL participates in Florida's net metering program, allowing customers to receive retail rate credits for excess solar energy sent to the grid. While FPL doesn't currently offer direct cash rebates, their net metering program provides ongoing financial benefits throughout the system's lifespan. Additionally, some local financing programs and solar loans with favorable terms are available to Fort Lauderdale residents, making solar installations more accessible with little to no upfront costs.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in Fort Lauderdale</h2>

<p>When selecting a solar installer in Fort Lauderdale, prioritize companies with proper Florida licensing, including electrical contractor licenses and solar contractor certifications. Look for installers with extensive experience in Broward County who understand local building codes, permitting requirements, and FPL interconnection procedures. Top-rated companies should offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels, 10-12 years for inverters) and workmanship (minimum 10 years). Verify the installer's Better Business Bureau rating, customer reviews, and financial stability to ensure long-term support. Choose companies that use Tier 1 solar panels from manufacturers like SunPower, Panasonic, or LG, and quality inverters from brands such as Enphase or SolarEdge. Professional installers should provide detailed system design, handle all permitting and inspections, coordinate FPL interconnection, and offer monitoring systems to track performance. Request multiple quotes and compare equipment specifications, warranties, and total system costs rather than just per-watt pricing.</p>

