<p>Solar panel systems in Fort Lauderdale typically achieve payback periods between 8-10 years, making them highly attractive investments. Based on FPL's 12.3¬¢/kWh rate and Fort Lauderdale's excellent solar resource, a typical 6kW system costing \$11,130 after the federal tax credit will generate approximately \$1,186 in annual electricity savings. Over 25 years, homeowners can expect total savings of \$29,650, representing a 266% return on investment. These calculations assume a modest 2% annual increase in electricity rates, which historically has been conservative for Florida. The financial benefits extend beyond direct savings, as solar installations typically increase home values by approximately 4% while providing energy independence and protection against rising utility costs. Fort Lauderdale's stable sunshine patterns and FPL's reliable net metering program make solar investments particularly secure, with most systems paying for themselves well before their 25-year warranty periods expire.</p>

